 The graph of $|x| + |2y|$ is a graph in the standard coordinate plane with the equation $|x| + |2y| = 10$. The coordinates of the given graph are (0, -10) and (0, 5).

[asy]
draw((0,-10)--(0,10));
label("y",(0,-10),W);
label("x",(0,10),N);
[/asy]

The y-coordinate at the leftmost point of the graph, which is negative, is -10. 

The x-coordinate at the rightmost point of the graph, which is positive, is 5.

The area of the rectangle formed by these two points is $A = 2 \cdot 10 = 20$.
The answer is: $20$.

